 American Institute of Architects Logo
The American Institute of Architects is a professional organization for architects in the United States. Headquartered in Washington, D.C., the AIA offers education, government advocacy, community redevelopment, and public outreach to support the architecture profession and improve its public image. The AIA also works with other members of the design and construction community to help coordinate the building industry. The AIA is currently headed by Robert Ivy, FAIA, as EVP/Chief Executive Officer and Peter Exley, FAIA, as 2021 AIA President.
You can download theAIAlogo on full-version of the page.
